अजीवित<BR>अजीवित n. (KARM. ex अ priv. et जोवित n. vita, a r.<BR>जीव् s. त) mors. BR. 2.31.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=004-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अज्ञातवास|अज्ञातवासः<BR>अज्ञातवास (ex अज्ञात a r. ज्ञा, et वास habitatio)<BR>1) m.<BR>KARM. incognita habitatio. IN. 5.57.<BR>2) Adj. BAH. incognitam<BR>habitationem habens, hinc Adv. अज्ञातवासम्<BR>incognitâ habitatione. NA. 15.20. 25.11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=004-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्च्|अंच्<BR>1. अञ्च् 1. P. A. (grammatici scribunt etiam अच्, gr. 110^a).)<BR>1) ire, in compositis ut प्राच्, quod in casibus fortibus<BR>sonat प्राञ्च्, v. gr. 196. sq.<BR>2) venerari, colere. — अञ्चित<BR>1) erectus, de pilis, v. apud Wils. रोमाञ्चित<BR>«having the hair of the body erect, considered as a proof of<BR>exquisite pleasure, enraptured, delighted».<BR>2) pulcher, de<BR>oculis, palpebris et superciliis, ubi primitive item «erectus»<BR>significare videtur: N. 12.45. अञ्चितेक्षण pulchros<BR>oculos habens; RAGH. 5.76. अञ्चिताक्षिपक्ष्मन्<BR>pulchras oculorum palpebras habens (Comment. Calc.<BR>{#aYcitAni sundarARi akznor netrayor pakzmARi<BR>yasya#}); अञ्चितभ्रू f. Wils. ed. 2. «a woman having beautifull<BR>eye brows».<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=004-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्च्|अंच्<BR>2. अञ्च् 10. P. (व्यक्तायाम् वाचि K. व्यक्तौ V.) clare, distincte<BR>loqui.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=004-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्चल|अंचलं|अंचलः|अञ्चलः<BR>अञ्चल n. (r. अञ्च् s. अल) finis, margo vestis. HIT. 83.8.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=004-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्चित|अंचित|अञ्चितः<BR>अञ्चित v. 1. अञ्च्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=004-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्चितपत्राक्ष<BR>अञ्चितपत्राक्ष (BAH. ex अञ्चितपत्र pulchra folia habens,<BR>quod hoc in composito lotum florem significare videtur,<BR>et अक्ष oculus) loto similes oculos habens. SU. 3.25.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=005-a" target="_blank">Page005-a+ 37</a>]<BR>Confirmari possit conjectura mea lectione ed. Calc.<BR>अञ्चितपद्माक्ष i. e. pulchro loto similes oculos habens.<BR>Fortasse tamen genuina lectio est अञ्चितपक्ष्माक्ष i. e.<BR>pulchris palpebris praeditos oculos habens; cf. supra<BR>memoratum अञ्चिताक्षिपक्ष्मन्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=004-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्छ्<BR>अञ्छ् 1. P. (आयामे, grammatici scribunt अछ्, gr. 110^a).)<BR>longum esse.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=005-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्ज्|अंज्<BR>अञ्ज् 7. 10. P. (अनज्मि, अञ्जयामि; अञ्ज् 10. a grammaticis<BR>scribitur अज्)<BR>1) ire, v. अञ्जस्.<BR>2) splendere.<BR>3) oblinere, ungere, praesertim cl. 10. MAN. 4.44.: {#aYjayantI<BR>svake netre#} oblinens oculos suos (lat. ungo).<BR>c. वि Caus.<BR>1) manifestare, arguere. MAN. 10.38. Pass.<BR>व्यज्यते (gr. 503. 538.). HIT. 103.20.<BR>2) creare. MAN. 1.6.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=005-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

