कलिङ्ग|कलिंग|कलिङ्गं|कलिङ्गः<BR>कलिङ्ग m. nomen regionis. DR. 2.7. (*)<BR>(*) Wils.: The name Calinga is applied in the Purânas<BR>to several places, but it especially signifies a district on<BR>the Coromandel coast, extending from below Cuttack to<BR>the vicinity of Madras.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=068-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

