खिद्<BR>2. खिद् 4. et 7. A.: खिद्ये, खिन्दे (खिद्ये etiam pro Pass.<BR>praecedentis haberi potest) dolore, moestitiâ affici,<BR>conturbari. HIT. 71.4.: {#sa puruzo yaH Kidyate ne<BR>'ndriyEH#}. - Part. pass. खिन्न<BR>1) dolore affectus, conturbatus.<BR>GITA-GOV. 3.7.: {#Kinnam asUyayA hfdayan<BR>tavA''kalayAmi#}; 3.2.: अनङ्गवाणव्रणखिन्नमानसः;<BR>UP. 19.<BR>2) fessus, fatigatus, languidus, confectus, exhaustus.<BR>MAN. 7.141. BHAR. 1.47. (Lith. źeidźiù laedo,<BR>offendo? gr. ϰῆδος fortasse pro ϰῇδος ex ϰειδος, ejecto<BR>ι et productâ vocali antecedente; v. खेद.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=098-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

