जॄ<BR>जॄ 1. 4. 9. 10. P. जरामि, जीर्यामि (gr. 330.), जृणामि (gr. 385.),<BR>जारयामि.<BR>1) conteri, consumi, confici, praesertim<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=141-b" target="_blank">Page141-b+ 36</a>]<BR>aetate. K.: जृणाति जरया जनः; Part. pass. जीर्ण<BR>senex, vetus, decrepitus. BH. 2.22.: वासांसि जीर्णानि;<BR>R. Schl. II.2.6.: {#jIrRasyA 'sya SarIrasya viSrAntim<BR>aBirocaye#}.<BR>2) concoquere, digerere. HIT. 5.14.: {#ajIrRe<BR>Bojanam vizam#}. — Caus. जरयामि et जारयामि concoquere,<BR>digerere. MAH. 1.2240.: {#jarayAmAsa tad (vizam)<BR>vIraH sahA 'nnena#}. (V. जरत्, जरा, जरित et cf. {#JF,<BR>jUr, jrI, jiri, cUrR, gUr#}, 2. कॄ, शॄ; hib. crionaim «I<BR>dry, wither, fade, dwindle», criona «old, ancient, prudent,<BR>sage» = जीर्ण; v. जरत्; fortasse lat. aeger huc<BR>pertinet, ita ut ae sit praepositio, quam ad अधि q. v. vel<BR>अति retulerim, ejectâ consonante; slav. зϱѣю ζrjejû<BR>maturesco, russ. зерно ζerno granum a conterendo<BR>dictum et formâ cum part. जीर्ण cohaerere videtur; lat.<BR>grânum fortasse per metathesin e gârnum = जीर्ण, quod<BR>ipsum e जार्ण, attenuato आ in ई, v. gr. 308., Vocalismus<BR>p. 214.; goth. kaurn, Th. kaurna pro kurna (gr. comp. 519.)<BR>e karna; nostrum Korn; lith. girna lapis molae<BR>manuariae, girnôs pl. mola manuaria; russ. жерновъ<BR>schernov lapis molaris; goth. qvairnus mola, germ. med.<BR>quirn, kurn, id.; cf. Pott. p. 228.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=141-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

