तूष्णीक|तूष्णीकः<BR>तूष्णीक (a तूष्णीम्, vel potius ab ejus themate तूष्णी, s.<BR>क) taciturnus. (Fortasse huc pertinet lith. tykas silens.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=156-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

तूष्णीम्<BR>तूष्णीम् Adv. (ut videtur, a perdito part. pass. तूष्ण, fem.<BR>तूष्णी, a r. तूष् s. न) tacite. DR. 9.24. BH. 2.9. (Russ.<BR>tisʽinà silentium, tranquillitas, tíchiĭ silens, tranquillus;<BR>lith. tylà silentium, tylù sileo, quorum l ex n ortum esse<BR>videtur, ejecto sʽ; hib. tosd «silence, taciturnity, quietness»,<BR>tosdadh «silencing, confutation», tosdaighim «I<BR>confute».)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=156-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

