दक्ष|दक्षः<BR>दक्ष (ut videtur, a r. दक्ष् s. अ)<BR>1) aptus, idoneus, habilis,<BR>dexter. BHAR. 1.58. N. 11.5.<BR>2) rectus, probus, honestus.<BR>BH. 12.16. SA. 1.3. (Primitive dexter, v. दक्षिण.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=162-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिण|दक्षिणः<BR>दक्षिण (v. gr. 279.; ut videtur, a r. दक्ष् s. इन्)<BR>1) dexter.<BR>SU. 4.12.<BR>2) meridionalis, quia meridionalis plaga ei qui<BR>ad orientem se convertit, a dexterâ est. H. 1.3. SU. 3.25.<BR>3) humanus, urbanus, comis. UR. 33.9.infr., v. दाक्षिण्य.<BR>दक्षिणेन Adv. ad meridiem. SU. 3.23. (Gr. δεξιός, δεξι-τεϱός;<BR>lat. dex-ter, dex-timus; hib. deas dexter, meridionalis;<BR>lith. dészinế f. dextera manus = दक्षिणा;<BR>goth. taîhsvô f. id.; germ. vet. zeso dexter, zesawa subst.<BR>f. dextera manus; fortasse russ. югъ jug merdionalis<BR>plaga; южный juschnyĭ meridionalis, abjecto d, sicut<BR>lat. Jupiter, Jovis e Diupiter, Diovis, gr. comp. 122.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=162-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणा<BR>1. दक्षिणा f. (fem. praec.)<BR>1) meridionalis plaga. DR. 3.7.<BR>2) merces, pretium educationis; RAGH. 5.20.; peracti sacrificii,<BR>BH. 17.13. RAGH. 4.86. in fine compp.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=162-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणा<BR>2. दक्षिणा Adv. (a दक्षिण s. आ) meridiem versus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=162-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दक्षिणापथ|दक्षिणापथः<BR>दक्षिणापथ m. (e praec. et पथ via in fine compp.) meridionalis<BR>regio Indiae. N. 9.23.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=162-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

