दत्ति|दत्तिः<BR>दत्ति f. (pro ददाति, abjecto आ, servatâ reduplicatione)<BR>donum. RAGH. 8.85. (Gr. δό-σις, lat. do-s, quod e dotis<BR>correptum esse videtur; hib. dath «a gift».)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दद्<BR>दद् 1. P. A. (proprie दद, forma reduplicata a rad. दा,<BR>correpto आ in अ, quod characteris 1^mae vel 6^tae classis<BR>analogiam sequitur, sicut a स्था venit तिष्ठति pro<BR>तिष्ठाति, a घ्रा जिघ्रति pro -घ्राति, v. gr. min. 295.) dare.<BR>MAH. 1.3482.: यौवनं स्वन् ददस्व; 3.10836.: {#Sarma<BR>dadasva#}; 2.1880.: शतानि चत्वार्य् अददद् धयानाम्;<BR>3.10207.: वेदीञ्चा ऽप्य् अददद् धैमीङ् कश्यपाय.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दध्<BR>दध् 1. A. (proprie दध, a rad. धा, correpto आ in अ, v.<BR>दद्) i. q. धा.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दधि<BR>दधि n. (fortasse a धे bibere, cum redupl.) lac coagulatum.<BR>(V. धे et cf. goth. daddja lacto.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्त|दंत|दंतः|दन्तः<BR>दन्त m. (ut mihi videtur, a r. अद् s. अन्त, ita ut mutilatum<BR>sit ex अदन्त) dens. H. 3.20. (Lith. dantis, goth.<BR>tunthus; germ. vet. zant, zand, zan; cambro-brit. dant;<BR>hib. déad; de lat. dens et gr. ὀδούς v. दत्; de russ.<BR>desnà gingiva v. दंष्ट्रा.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्तच्छद|दंतच्छद|दन्तच्छदः<BR>दन्तच्छद m. (e praec. et छद tegens) labium. ĆAUR. 13.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्तिन्|दंतिन्<BR>दन्तिन् m. (a दन्त s. इन्, dentatus) elephantus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्ध्<BR>दन्ध् 1. P. (पालने K., scribitur दध्; equidem दन्ध् vel<BR>potius दन्ध reduplicatione explicaverim e धा, correpto<BR>आ in अ et insertâ nasali; v. दद्, दध्) sustentare,<BR>nutrire.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दन्व्<BR>दन्व् 1. P. (व्रजे; scribitur दव्; gr. 110^a).) ire; cf. {#du, Danv,<BR>DAv#}; gr. δονέω = Caus. दन्वयामि.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दभ्<BR>दभ्<BR>1) 10. P. दभयामि (नोदे K.) mittere.<BR>2) 1. P. in dial.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">Page163-b+ 37</a>]<BR>Vêd. laedere, occidere, v. दम्भ् cl. 5. RIGV. 84.20.:<BR>मा त ऊतयो वसो ऽस्मान् कदाचना दभन् «non tua<BR>auxilia, domicilii largitor! nos unquam perire sinant»;<BR>Vv. 32.12. (v. Westerg. s. r. दम्भ्): {#na tan daBanti<BR>ripaH#} (hostes). — Desid. in dial. Vêd. दिप्स् (e दिधप्स्<BR>ejectâ syllabâ ध) laedendi, occidendi cupidum esse.<BR>RIGV. 25.14.: न यन् दिप्सन्ति दिप्सवः «quem<BR>deum non caedere affectant caedendi cupidi»; Vv. (v.<BR>Westerg. s. r. दम्भ्): यो नो दिवा दिप्सति यश्च नक्तम्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्<BR>1. दम् 4. P. दाम्यामि domare. BHATT. 18.20.: {#yamo dAmyati<BR>rAkzasAn#}. Part. pass. दान्त domitus, mansuetus.<BR>BR. 1.25. SU. 2.17. — Caus. दमयामि i. q. primit.<BR>MAH. 1.2995.: सर्वन् दमयत्य् असौ; ibd. 5537.:<BR>सौवीरम् अदमयच् छरैः. (Goth. TAM decere, ga-timith,<BR>ga-tam; germ. vet. zimit decet, zam decuit; fortasse<BR>lat. damnum. Ad Caus. दमयामि referimus gr. δαμάω, δαμάζω,<BR>lat. domo, goth. tamja, nostrum zähme,<BR>zahm, v. gr. comp. 19. 109^a).6.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्<BR>2. दम् Indecl. (r. दम्) uxor in comp. दम्पती uxor et maritus.<BR>SA. 6.3. (V. 2. जम् et cf. gr. δάμαϱ.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम|दमः<BR>दम m. (r. दम् s. अ)<BR>1) domitus, refrenatio, sedatio perturbationum<BR>animi. IN. 4.7. N. 6.10. BH. 10.4. 16.1.<BR>2) poena, mulcta. MAN. 8.59.<BR>3) in fine compp. domans,<BR>domitor.<BR>4) nom. pr. N. 1.9. (Gr. -δαμος, ἱππόδαμος<BR>sicut scr. अरिन्दम.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमन|दमनं|दमनः<BR>दमन m. (r. दम् s. अन) domitor; nom. pr. N. 1.9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दमयन्ती|दमयंती<BR>दमयन्ती f. (part. praes. Causativi दमयामि, v. दम्) quae<BR>domat; nom. pr. N. 1.9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्पती<BR>दम्पती v. 2. दम्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्भ्|दंभ्<BR>1. दम्भ् 10. P. (नोदे, scribitur दभ्, gr. 110^a).) mittere; v.<BR>टिप्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्भ्|दंभ्<BR>2. दम्भ् 5. P. दभ्नोमि.<BR>1) fallere, decipere, e. c. {#daBnoti<BR>DUrtaH#} K.<BR>2) laedere, occidere, praesertim in dial.<BR>Vêd. NIGH. 2.19. (v. Westerg.) दभ्नोति (वधः);<BR>RIGV. 24.10.: अदब्धानि वरुणस्य व्रतानि; 41.1.:<BR>यं रक्षन्ति प्रचेतसो वरुणो मित्रो अर्यमा । नूचित् स<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=164-a" target="_blank">Page164-a+ 36</a>]<BR>दभ्यते जनः «quem protegunt dii Varunus, Mitrus, Aryamanus,<BR>non sane laeditur ille vir» (नूचित् = नै ऽव,<BR>v. Westerg.); YAJURV. 1.31. (Westerg.): {#adabDena<BR>tvA cakzuzA 'vapaSyAmi#} (दभ्नोति, दब्ध, दभ्यते<BR>etiam ad दभ् referri possunt. Cf. तुभ् et v. दल्भ).<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=163-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्भ|दंभ|दंभः|दम्भः<BR>दम्भ m. (r. दम्भ् s. अ) fraus, simulatio; superbia. BH. 16.4.<BR>IN. 5.62. MAH. 2.877. (V. दल्भ.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=164-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दम्य|दम्यः<BR>दम्य m. (r. दम् s. य) taurus juvencus. RAGH. 6.78.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=164-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दय्<BR>दय् 1. A. (गतौ दाने हिंसायाम् आदाने K. {#grahaRe gatO<BR>vaDe, dAne avane#} V.) ire, dare, laedere, occidere, sumere,<BR>tueri. दयित amatus. IN. 1.7. 3.4. N. 16.28. (Cf.<BR>दे, hib. deidh f. «desire, longing», deidh m. «a protector,<BR>defender», deide «obedience, submission».)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=164-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

