दृह्<BR>दृह् 1. P. (वृद्धौ) crescere. Part. pass. दृहित qui crevit,<BR>et दृढ (gr. 618.) extensus, multus, firmus, solidus. SU. 1.10. 18.<BR>N. 6.10. M. 30. — दृढम् Adv. valde. N. 23.8.<BR>A. 8.1. (V. दृंह्, दीर्घ, 2. तृह् et cf. hib. daingean<BR>«strong, secure, close»; daingne «strength, stability»;<BR>Pottius apte huc trahit anglo-sax. telg planta, virgultum,<BR>et goth. tulgjan firmare, roborare, Etym. Forsch. I.251.;<BR>gr. δϱιάω, δϱίος, v. Benf. I.96.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=175-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दॄ<BR>1. दॄ 9. P. दृणामि, part. pass. दीर्ण (gr. 385. 609.) lacerare,<BR>dilacerare, dissecare, rumpere, findere. MAH. 3.16426.:<BR>ब्रह्मास्त्रेण ददारा ऽद्रिम्; H. 4.8.: शिरो राक्षस दीर्यताम्;<BR>N. 21.15.: हृदयन् दीर्यत इदं शोकात्. — Caus.<BR>findere, proprie facere ut alqd findatur. R. Schl. I.16.24.:<BR>दारयेयुः क्षितिम् पद्भ्याम्; MAH. 1.795.: {#vajran<BR>tad vilam adArayat#}. (Vera rad. forma est दर्, unde<BR>दल् q. v.; cf. gr. δέϱω; slav. derû excorio; russ. dra-tj<BR>rumpere, seindere, dratj koschu detrahere pellem; goth.<BR>ga-TAR (ga-taira, ga-tar) dirumpere, scindere; angl.<BR>tear; germ. vet. ZAR (ziru, zar); nostrum zehre, zerre.)<BR>c. अव i. q. simpl. MAH. 3.17300.: {#hfdayam avadIryate<BR>me#}. — Caus. findere. RAGH. 13.3.: उर्वीम् अवदारयद्भिः.<BR>c. अव praef. वि id. R. Schl. II.72.28.: {#vyavadIrRam mano<BR>mama#}.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=175-b" target="_blank">Page175-b+ 36</a>]<BR>c. वि id. MAH. 1.1477.: प्रहारैर् देवान् विददार; 3.673.:<BR>जालं विदीर्य; N. 9.4.: मन्युना व्यदीर्यते ऽव हृदयम्;<BR>19.3. — Caus. id. BHAG. 1.19.: {#sa Gozo…hfdayAni<BR>vyadArayat#}.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=175-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

