नाध्<BR>नाध् 1. P. A. i. q. नाथ्. RIGV. 118.10.: नाधमानाः «opes<BR>desiderantes»; 110.5.: उपमन् नाधमानाः «sufficientem<BR>sibi cibum optantes»; 109.3.: इति नाधमानाः<BR>«sic precantes». (V. नाथ्.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=193-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नाना<BR>नाना Indecl. (ut videtur, reduplicatio stirpis demonstr. न,<BR>quae invenitur in fine pron. compp. अन, एन, producto<BR>अ) multus, varius. H. 1.19. BH. 11.5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=193-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

नान्दी|नांदी<BR>नान्दी f. (r. नन्द् s. ई) benedictio, a qua incipit prologus<BR>dramatum. UR. 1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=193-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

