पल्लव|पल्लवं|पल्लवः<BR>पल्लव m. n. gemma arboris; surculus. N. 12.102. Lass. 59.9. 10.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पल्वल|पल्वलं<BR>पल्वल m. n. palus, lacus, stagnum. N. 12.8. 85. (Cf. lat.<BR>palus, palûd-is.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवन|पवनं|पवनः<BR>पवन (r. पू s. अन)<BR>1) n. purificatio. HIT. 108.13.<BR>2) m.<BR>ventus. N. 24.40. (De cambro-brit. fwn, quod Pictetius<BR>huc trahit, v. प्राण.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवमान|पवमानः<BR>पवमान m. (purificans, Part. praes. ATM. rad. पू) ventus.<BR>AM.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पवित्र|पवित्रं|पवित्रः<BR>पवित्र (r. पू s. त्र inserto इ)<BR>1) Adj. purus, purificatus.<BR>BH. 4.38.<BR>2) n. aqua. (Hib. beathra «water», fothragaim<BR>«I bathe, cleanse», fothragadh «a bath, well of<BR>purification».)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पश्<BR>1. पश् 1. P. A. 10. P. (पशामि, पशे, पाशयामि) ligare.<BR>(V. पाश et cf. पष्, स्पश्; cambro-brit. fasgu<BR>«to bind, or tie in a bundle», fasgiad «a ligation, a<BR>tying in a bundle»; gr. πήγνυμι; lat. pango, fascia, fortasse<BR>etiam fas huc pertinet sicut jus a Pottio apte ad<BR>यु ligare refertur; russ. pojas cingulum, nisi po est<BR>praep.; v. Pott. 1.267.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पश्<BR>2. पश् 4. P. (in tempp. specialibus tantum usurpatur et a<BR>grammaticis Indicis in radices non receptum est)<BR>videre, v. दृश्. (Hib. faicim «I see», feachaim «I look,<BR>view», faochog «oculus»; lat. specio, praefixo s, fortasse<BR>e praep. सम्, nisi पश् corruptum e स्पश्, v. 1. पश्;<BR>germ. vet. spêho speculor; gr. σκέπτω, mutatâ lab. in<BR>gutt. et vice versâ, v. Pott. p. 267.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पशु|पशुः<BR>पशु m. (ut videtur, a r. पश् ligare s. उ, sicut fortasse lat.<BR>bestia a बन्ध् ligare, mutato ध् in s sicut in zendico<BR>baśta ligatus, v. gr. comp. 102.) animal, pecus. HIT. 5.21. 22.<BR>H. 4.54. (Lat. pecus, boruss. vet. pecku, germ.<BR>vet. fihu, nostrum Vieh.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पश्चात्<BR>पश्चात् Adv. (Ablat. ab inusitato पश्च, a quo etiam पश्चिम<BR>descendit)<BR>1) pone, a tergo. MEGH. 37. (Schol. पृष्ठदेशे).<BR>2) occidentem versus. MEGH. 16.<BR>3) retro. SAK. 26.7.<BR>UR. 60.15.<BR>4) postea, in posterum, deinde. N. 18.7. 21.28.;<BR>— ततः पश्चात् inde, ab hoc, ab illo tempore [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-a" target="_blank">Page214-a+ 37</a>]<BR>in posterum, deinde, postea. H. 4.16. N. 18.18.<BR>(Cf. lith. paskuy postea, paskuttinnis, paskiausas ultimus;<BR>boruss. vet. pans-dan postea, quod suffixo convenit cum<BR>pirsdan antea. Fortasse etiam lith. pas prope et lat. post<BR>huc pertinent. Hib. feasd, feasda «hereafter, henceforward,<BR>forthwith» fortasse a lat. post, postea.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=213-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पश्चात्कृ<BR>पश्चात्कृ (e पश्चात् et कृ facere) superare. RAGH. 17.18.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पश्चात्ताप|पश्चात्तापः<BR>पश्चात्ताप m. (e पश्चात् et ताप) poenitentia. AM.; HIT. 33.19.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पश्चिम|पश्चिमं|पश्चिमः<BR>पश्चिम Adj. (a पश्च - v. पश्चात् - suff. इम)<BR>1) posticus,<BR>posterior.<BR>2) occidentalis. SU. 3.26. N. 13.5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पा<BR>1. पा 1. P. (पिवामि in dial. Vêd. पिबामि e पिपामि, v.<BR>gr. min. 295.; gerund. पीत्वा; Pass. पीये; part. पीत)<BR>bibere. MAN. 11.8.: सोमम् पिवति; H. 1.52.: {#pAsyantI<BR>'me jalam#}; RAGH. 2.19.: तम् पपौ सा लोचनाभ्याम्;<BR>H. 1.27.: पीत्वा पानीयम्; 4.16.; DR. 6.5.:<BR>पीतरसश्च कुम्भः; HIT. 6.8.: {#ayam agadaH kin na<BR>pIyate#}. — Caus. पाययामि pro पापयामि (gr. 519.)<BR>bibere dare, potionem dare. MAH. 1.192.: हयान् पाययित्वा.<BR>(Gr. ΠΩ, πέπωϰα, πῶϑι, ἐπόϑην; attenuato<BR>आ in ῑ: πίνω, πῖϑι, cf. पीत, पीये et v. पी; lat. PŌ,<BR>pô-tum = पातुम्, pô-turus = पातृ, po-culum, bibo<BR>= पिवामि; lith. pếnas lac, v. पान; boruss. vet. pouton<BR>bibere; russ. pi-tj id., pívo cerevisia; germ. vet. bier;<BR>anglo-sax. beor id.; hib. pótaim «I drink», nisi hoc a<BR>lat. poto.)<BR>c. अनु i. q. simpl. RAGH. 8.67.<BR>c. आ id. MAH. 2.2302.: आपिवेयन् तस्य रुधिरं युधि.<BR>(Pottius apte huc trahit vocem अप् aqua, in casibus fortibus<BR>आप्.)<BR>c. प्र id. H. 2.11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पा<BR>2. पा 2. P. (रक्षणे; Pass. पाये, Caus. पालयामि) servare,<BR>tueri, sustentare. RAM. I.13.18.: नः पाहि राक्षसात्;<BR>GHAT. 12.: {#SokasAgare 'dya pAtitAn tvadguRasmaraRam<BR>eva pAti tAm#}; RAGH. 2.48.: {#upaplaveByaH<BR>prajAH pAsi#}. (V. प, पति, पल्, पाल्, पात्र et<BR>cf. lat. PĀ in pâ-vi, pâ-bulum; gr. (πάομαι) ἐπᾱσάμην,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-b" target="_blank">Page214-b+ 37</a>]<BR>πέπᾱμαι; πατέομαι tam huc quam ad पा bibere trahi<BR>potest, correpto आ, adjecto τ, v. gr. comp. 109^b).1.;<BR>πάτνη, πάϑνη, ϕάϑνη; δεσ-πό-της, cujus prima syllaba<BR>ad scr. दिश् trahi posset; fortasse ἄνϑϱωπος primitive<BR>significat viros regens, ita ut conveniat cum<BR>नृप q. v. et ἄνϑϱω-πος sit pro ἄνδϱο-πος producto ο<BR>et mutato δ in ϑ; lith. po-nas dominus, pé-nas pabulum,<BR>pastus, cibus; pénù pasco, cibo; russ. pitáju id.;<BR>goth. fôdja id., fôdeins cibus; nostrum Futter.)<BR>c. परि i. q. simpl. DEV. 11.32.: त्वम् परिपासि विश्वम्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

पांशु|पांशुः<BR>पांशु m. pulvis. N. 13.28. (V. पांसु et cf. cambro-brit.<BR>pain «bloom, fine powder, or dust»; v. Pict. p. 15.; lat.<BR>pulvis pro pulcvis, mutato n in l, adjecto i, sicut e. c. in<BR>levis pro leguis = लघु, v. Ag. Benary Römische Lautlehre<BR>p. 209.; lith. pếska arena.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=214-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

