भक्ष्य|भक्ष्यं<BR>भक्ष्य (r. भक्ष् s. य)<BR>1) Adj. edendus.<BR>2) m. cibus. H. 2.8.<BR>N. 9.13. (Goth. basi, them. basja n. bacca.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=241-1b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भग|भगं|भगः<BR>भग m. (r. भज् s. अ)<BR>1) portio.<BR>2) bona fortuna, felicitas,<BR>beatitudo.<BR>3) vulva. AM. (Huc vel ad भाग traxerim<BR>goth. ga-bigs dives, ita ut proprie significet qui cum<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=242-a" target="_blank">Page242-a+ 37</a>]<BR>divitiis est, them. ga-biga = सभग; cf. etiam lith.<BR>nabagas homo miser, pauper, na = scr. न non; bagotas<BR>dives; russ. û-bogiĭ pauper, bogatyĭ dives; cf. Pott. pp. 235. 236.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=241-1b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्|भगवन्त्<BR>भगवत् (a भग s. वत्) felix, beatus, excelsus, excellens,<BR>praeclarus, venerabilis. SU. 3.24. 4.23. BH. 10.14. RAGH. 8.80.<BR>(Cf. slav. bog deus.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=242-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

