भ्रष्ट|भ्रष्टं<BR>भ्रष्ट (a r. भ्रंश्, v. gr. 615.) v. भ्रंश्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=252-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ्रष्टाभरणकेशान्त<BR>भ्रष्टाभरणकेशान्त (BAH. e भ्रष्ट elapsus et DVANDV.<BR>आभरणकेशान्त, आभरण + केशान्त, केश et<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=253-a" target="_blank">Page253-a+ 27</a>]<BR>अन्त (*)) elapsa ornamenta et capillos habens. SU. 1.15.<BR>(*) केशान्त idem significare videtur ac केश, cf. सुभ्रूनासाक्षिकेशान्त.<BR>H. 3.14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=252-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ्रश्<BR>भ्रश् v. भ्रंश्.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=253-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ्राज्<BR>भ्राज् 1. P. A. lucere, splendere. H. 4.40.: {#baBrAjatur yaTA<BR>SElO nIhAreRA 'BisamvftO#}; N. 2.29.: {#BrAjamanaM yaTA<BR>ravim#}. (Cf. राज्; gr. ϕλέγω, ϕέγγω; lat. fulgeo,<BR>flam-ma e flag-ma, flagro; goth. BAIRH, unde bairhtei<BR>lux et Denom. bairh-tja manifesto; anglo-sax. blican<BR>splendere; angl. brigh-t; germ. vet. blich, blic, blig fulmen,<BR>lumen, bleih pallidus (nostrum bleich), blanch candidus,<BR>blinchan lucere; lith. blizgù scintillo, radio; russ.<BR>blesʽću splendeo; scot. boillsg «splendor, fulgor», boillsgeach<BR>«coruscus, emicans, fulgidus, splendeus».)<BR>c. वि i. q. simpl. DR. 1.9.: विभ्राजमानाम् वपुषा.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=253-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भ्रातृ<BR>भ्रातृ m. (rad. incerta, suff. तृ, v. gr. 178. annot.) frater.<BR>(Goth. brôthar; lat. frâter; gr. ϕϱᾱτήϱ, ϕϱάτωϱ; hib.<BR>brathair; russ. brat; lith. brolis mutilatum esse videtur<BR>e brotris, ejecto t, mutato r in l.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=253-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

