मन्द्|मंद्<BR>मन्द् 1. A. (scribitur मद्, gr. 110^a).) in dial. Vêd.<BR>1) gaudere.<BR>RIGV. 26.5.: अस्य नो मन्दस्व सख्यस्यच<BR>«hoc nostro sacrificio gaude, consortioque»; 51.12.: {#yezu<BR>mandase#} «quibus gaudes». PAR. exhilarare. RIGV. V.<BR>(v. Westerg.): सोमो मन्दतु त्वा.<BR>2) laudari, celebrari.<BR>RIGV. 51.11.: {#mandizwayad uSane kAvye sacA<BR>indraH#} «cum laudaretur Indras ipsum desiderante carmine».<BR>3) dormire. RIGV. V. (v. Westerg.): {#agne tvaM<BR>sujAgfhi vayaM sumandizImahi#}. — Caus. exhilarare.<BR>RIGV. 4.7. (Cf. मण्ड्, मद्, मुद्, वन्द्; germ. vet.<BR>menden gaudere e mandjan, praet. manta; mendi gaudium;<BR>hib. meadhrach «glad, joyful, merry», meadhradh<BR>«mirth, song, melody», molaim «I praise».)<BR>c. उत् exhilarare. RIGV. 8.6.: {#ut tvA sutAso raBasA<BR>amandizuH#} «te parata libamina cito inebriantia laetificarunt».<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=259-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मन्द|मंद|मन्दः<BR>मन्द (r. मन्द् s. अ)<BR>1) paucus. मन्दम् Adv. parum, paululum.<BR>N. 16.8. DR. 3.1.<BR>2) tardus.<BR>3) stultus, stolidus.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=259-b" target="_blank">Page259-b+ 37</a>]<BR>N. 15.10. 14. (Hib. mall «slow, dilatory, tardy, tedious,<BR>prolix».)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=259-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

