मृ<BR>मृ 6. A. interdum P. (nisi potius cl. 4., v. gramm. min. 299.)<BR>mori. BH. 2.20.: न जायते म्रियते वा; N. 13.38.: {#nA<BR>'prAptakAlo mriyate#}; BR. 1.34.: मरिष्यन्ति मया विना;<BR>2.19.: मरिष्यामि; 3.9.: म्रियेयम्. — मृत mortuus.<BR>Subst. n. mors. BR. 1.35. — Caus. occidere. MAH. 1.7276.:<BR>ततो यमः…ना ऽमारयत् कञ्चित्. (Lat. morior,<BR>morbus; gr. βϱοτός pro μϱοτός = मृत e मर्त,<BR>ἀ-μβϱοσία pro ἀ-μϱοσία, cf. अमृत; lith. mirsztu morior,<BR>praet. mirriau, fut. mir-su, infin. mir-ti; s-mertis<BR>mors; russ. u-miraju morior, mertvyĭ mortuus, s-mer-tj<BR>mors. Ad Caus. मारयामि trahimus hib. marbhaim «I<BR>kill, slay», marbhan «a corpse, dead body» etc.; goth.<BR>maur-thr caedes.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=269-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

