मोक्ष्<BR>मोक्ष् 1. et 10. P. interdum A. solvere, liberare. H. 2.34.:<BR>एतान्…मोक्षयिष्याम्य् अहङ् कामं राक्षसात्; N. 11.29.:<BR>मोक्षयित्वा स ताम् व्याधः; MAH. 1.3917.: {#jAtaY<BR>jAtam mokzayizye janmato mAnuzAt#}. (Cf. मुच्,<BR>unde मोक्ष् adjectâ sibilante cum Gunâ.)<BR>c. वि i. q. simpl. MAH. 1.7880.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=272-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोक्ष|मोक्षः<BR>मोक्ष m. (r. मोक्ष् s. अ) solutio, liberatio. BH. 18.30. 7.29.<BR>praesertim animae liberatio a sensuum vinculis, a corporis<BR>gaudiis vel doloribus, aequanimitas. BR. 1.17. BH. 5.28.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=272-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मोघ|मोघं|मोघः<BR>मोघ (r. मुह् mutato ह् in घ् - cf. gr. 357. - suff. अ) vanus,<BR>irritus. SA. 5.49. — मोघम् Adv. frustra. BH. 3.16.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=272-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

