रत्नसङ्घातमय<BR>रत्नसङ्घातमय (fem. ई, e रत्नसङ्घात gemmarum vel<BR>margaritarum cumulus, suff. मय) quod e gemmarum<BR>vel margaritarum cumulo constat. SU. 3.14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथ|रथः<BR>रथ m. (ut videtur, a r. ऋ s. थ)<BR>1) currus. N. 19.20.<BR>2) heros.<BR>DR. 3.7. 7.3. (Lith. rátas rota = nom. रथस्; lat.<BR>rota; germ. vet. rad n., Them. rada id.; hib. roth id.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथाङ्ग|रथांग|रथाङ्गं|रथाङ्गः<BR>रथाङ्ग (e रथ et अङ्ग membrum)<BR>1) n. rota.<BR>2) nomen avis,<BR>anas casarea, the ruddy goose. UR. 67.7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथिन्<BR>रथिन् m. (a रथ s. इन्) curru praeditus, currus dominus,<BR>possessor, curru vectus. DR. 2.12. N. 19.23.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रथोपस्थ|रथोपस्थः<BR>रथोपस्थ v. उपस्थ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रद्<BR>रद् 1. P. findere, fodere. — रद् dara, in dial. Vêd. ortum<BR>esse videtur e दद् mutato द् in र्. RIGV. 116.7. 117.11.<BR>(V. रद, रदन dens et cf. म्रद्, मृद्, lat. rôdo,<BR>ros-trum.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रद|रदः<BR>रद (r. रद् s. अ)<BR>1) Adj. findens. GHAT. 1.<BR>2) m. dens.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रदन|रदनः<BR>रदन m. (r. रद् s. अन) dens. AM.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रदनच्छद|रदनच्छदः|रदनछद<BR>रदनच्छद m. (e praec. et छद tegens) labium. AM.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रध्<BR>रध् 4. P. रध्यामि, praet. mtf. अरन्धम्, praet. redupl. ररन्ध,<BR>fut. aux. रत्स्यामि et रधिष्यामि.<BR>1) occidi, perire.<BR>RIGV. V. (v. Westerg.): {#SatravaH rAraDuz we (= raranDus<BR>te)#}.<BR>2) ferire, laedere, occidere. BHATT. 9.29.:<BR>अक्षं रधितुम् आरेभे रद्धा लङ्कानिवासिनाम् (Schol.<BR>हिंसितुम्). — Caus. रन्धयामि ferire, laedere, vexare,<BR>occidere. R. Schl. II.81.3.: {#BarataM Sokasantaptam BUyaH<BR>SokEr aranDayat#}; RIGV. 51.6.: {#aranDayo 'tiTigvAya<BR>SamBaram#} «necasti propter festum, hospitibus visitandum,<BR>Sambharam». (Cf. वध्, वाध्; lat. laedo.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रन्ध्र|रंध्र|रंध्रं<BR>रन्ध्र (fortasse a r. रध्, insertâ nasali, suff. र) n. cava, caverna,<BR>fissura. MEGH. 43. 58. P. 14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रप्<BR>रप् 1. P.<BR>1) loqui.<BR>2) in dial. Vêd. laudare. RIGV. 119.9.:<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-b" target="_blank">Page286-b+ 37</a>]<BR>उत स्या वाम् मधुमन्मक्षिका ऽरपत् «etiam illa vos<BR>mellifica apis laudavit». (Cf. लप्.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रफ्<BR>रफ् 1. P. (गत्याम् K. गत्याम् वधे V.) ire; occidere. Cf.<BR>रम्फ्, रर्क्, रम्ब्, सृप् i. e. सर्प्; lat. repo, serpo.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रभ्<BR>रभ् 1. A. (रभे, 3. per. sing. praet. mef. Pass. अरम्भि; Caus.<BR>रम्भयामि) c. आ incipere. R. Schl. I.12.37.: {#karmARy<BR>AreBire#}; MAN. 9.300.: {#AraBetE 'va karmARi…karmARy<BR>AraBamARaM hi puruzaM SrIr nizevate#}; BH. 18.25.: {#mohAd<BR>AraByate karma#}; BHATT. 15.58.: {#akroDi kumBakarRena<BR>pezwum aramBica kzitO#}. — Part. आरब्ध tam<BR>active quam passive usurpatur.<BR>1) qui incepit. SU. 2.9.<BR>N. 14.12.<BR>2) coeptus. SA. 4.5. N. 5.21. (Simplex रभ्<BR>primitive capere significare videtur, cf. लभ्,<BR>λαμβάνω, lat. rabies, v. praef. सम्.)<BR>c. आ praef. अनु capere, accipere, recipere. R. Schl. II.64.60.:<BR>{#yadi mAM saMspfSed rAmaH sakfd anvAraBeta<BR>vA Danam vA yOvarAjyam vA jIveyam#}.<BR>c. आ praef. अभि incipere. MAH. 3.10724.<BR>c. आ praef. प्र id. BH. 18.15.: कर्म प्रारभते.<BR>c. आ praef. सम् id. R. Schl. I.45.13.: {#AKyAtun tat<BR>samAreBe#}.<BR>c. परि amplecti. GITA-GOV. 1.38.: हरिम् परिरभ्य सरागम्;<BR>2.13. — Desid. amplecti cupere. RAGH. 13.32.:<BR>परिरिप्समानः.<BR>c. सम् संरब्ध<BR>1) perturbatus. N. 13.14.<BR>2) iratus, furens.<BR>HIT. 4.23. R. Schl. II.55.30.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रम्<BR>रम् 1. A. interdum P. praet. mltf. अरंसि, fut. aux. रंस्ये.<BR>1) se delectare, voluptate frui, gaudere, oblectari. IN. 3.8.:<BR>स तेन सह सड्गम्य रेमे पार्थः; 5.60.: {#citrasenena<BR>sahitaH…reme sa svargasadane#}; N. 5.43.: {#avApya nArIratnam…reme<BR>saha tayA#}; 15.7.: एताभ्यां रंस्यसे सार्धम्;<BR>BH. 10.9.: तुष्यन्तिच रमन्तिच. C. loc. rei. BH. 5.22.:<BR>न तेषु रमते बुधः. — रत delectatus, laetus, gaudens,<BR>c. loc. N. 5.32. BH. 2.42. 12.4.<BR>2) ludere. BHATT. 6.15.:<BR>मा रंस्था जीवितेन नः. — Caus. रमयामि<BR>1) exhilarare.<BR>IN. 5.4.: रमयन्ती ऽव फाल्गुनम्; 5.43.: {#tapasA<BR>ramayanty asmAn#}.<BR>2) se delectare, gaudere, oblectari. [<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=287-a" target="_blank">Page287-a+ 36</a>]<BR>MAH. 3.11371.: पिवन्ति रमयन्तिच. — Intens.<BR>रंरम्, in dial. Vêd. रारम्. RIGV. 91.13.: {#rAranDi<BR>no hfdi#}. (Hib. reamhain «pleasure»; lith. ramù quietus,<BR>tranquillus, rim-ti quiescere, v. praef. आ, उप, वि;<BR>gr. ἠϱέμα.)<BR>c. अभि i. q. simpl. IN. 5.62.<BR>c. आ<BR>1) id. MAN. 4.175.<BR>2) desinere, quiescere. MAN. 2.73.:<BR>विरामो ऽस्त्व् इतिचा ऽऽरमेत्.<BR>c. आ praef. उप<BR>1) i. q. simpl. MAH. 1.4183.<BR>3) requiescere,<BR>desinere, desistere. H. 4.53.: {#pariSrAntaH sADu tAvad<BR>upArama#}; RAGH. 16.3.: रेषान् दानप्रवृत्तेर् अनुपारतानाम्.<BR>c. उप requiescere, desinere, cessare. BH. 2.20.: {#yatro 'paramate<BR>cittam#}; MAH. 1.2174.: हलहलाशब्दः उपरराम;<BR>R. Schl. II.3.5.: राज्ञस् तू ऽपरते वाक्ये. Cum ablat. BH. 2.35.:<BR>रणाद् उपरतः.<BR>c. नि i. q. simpl. N. 6.10. MAN. 3.45.<BR>c. वि<BR>1) quiescere, desinere, desistere. MAH. 1.8475.:<BR>{#pAvakaSca tadA dAvan dagDvA…ahAni paYcacE 'kaYca<BR>virarAma#}. Cum ablat. UR. 32.16.: विरम संरम्भात्;<BR>RAGH. 8.22.: विरराम कर्मणः.<BR>2) silere. MAH. 1.8112.:<BR>एतावद् उक्त्वा वचनम् विरराम स पार्थिवः; 2.1401.<BR>R. Schl. I.21.20.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=286-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रमण|रमणं|रमणः<BR>रमण m. (r. रम् s. अन) amator. UR. 64.3.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=287-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

रमणीय|रमणीयं<BR>रमणीय (r. रम् s. अनीय, v. euphon. r. 94^a).) amoenus. H. 1.24.<BR>N. 5.45.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=287-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

