वन्द्|वंद्<BR>वन्द् 1. A. interdum P. (scribitur वद्, gr. 110^a).)<BR>1) se inclinare<BR>reverentiae causâ, inclinato corpore salutare. DR. 9.19.:<BR>ववन्दे…मुनिम्; A. 1.5.: {#vfkodarasyA 'pi<BR>vavanda pAdO#}; 2.: युधिष्ठिरम्…अवन्दत; MAH. 2.23.:<BR>ववन्दे चरणौ मूर्ध्ना…पितृष्वसुः (v. 2. वद् praef.<BR>अभि).<BR>2) laudare, celebrare. R. Schl. II.16.37.: {#rAmam<BR>…vacoBir agryEH…vavandire#}. (Fortasse lat. laus,<BR>laud-is mutato v in l, n in u, v. gr. comp. 20. 255. 9.)<BR>c. अभि i. q. simpl. sgnf. 1. R. ed. Ser. I.28.34.: {#rAGavAv<BR>aByavandatAm#}.<BR>c. सम् id. MAH. 1.5420.: तम्…शिरसा समवन्दत.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=308-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

