शरधि|शरधिः<BR>शरधि m. (e शर sagitta et धि tenens, v. इषुधि) pharetra.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=345-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

शरभ|शरभः<BR>शरभ m. animalis species (*). DR. 4.13.<BR>(*) Wilson:<BR>1) A fabulous animal, supposed to have<BR>eight legs and to inhabit particularly the snowy mountains.<BR>AM.<BR>2) A young elephant.<BR>3) A monkey in Rama's army.<BR>MED.<BR>4) A camel.<BR>5) A grasshopper. AM.<BR>6) A locust. (V.<BR>शलभ et cf. gr. ϰάϱαβος.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=345-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

