श्वन्<BR>श्वन् m. (in casibus debilissimis शुन्, v. gr. 225.) canis.<BR>(Gr. ϰύων, ϰυνός = शुनस्; lat. cani-s, ejecto v vel u,<BR>addito i, sed gen. pl. can-um a primitivo Them. in n, sicut<BR>juven-um a juven = युवन्; lith. nom. szů = श्वा,<BR>gen. szun-s = शुनस्, v. gr. comp. 139.; hib. nom. cu,<BR>gen. et pl. coin; goth. hund-s, Them. hunda, adjecto da;<BR>russ. sobaka pro sbaka, cf. med. σπαϰα apud Herod.<BR>«τὴν γάϱ ϰύνα ϰαλέουσι σπάϰα Μῆδοι», pers. سك<BR>seg, zend. nom. 𐬯𐬞𐬀 śpâ, acc. 𐬯𐬞𐬁𐬥𐬆𐬨 śpânĕm,<BR>(v. gr. comp. 50.).)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=359-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

