षष्<BR>षष् (in initio comp. et nom. acc. षट्, v. gr. 74. et 256.)<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=361-a" target="_blank">Page361-a+ 19</a>]<BR>sex. (षष् e क्षष् mutilatum esse videtur, cf. zend.<BR> 𐬒𐬱𐬎𐬎𐬀𐬱 csvas, lat. sex, gr. ἕξ, anglo-sax. sex,<BR>germ. vet. sehs e sihs, goth. saihs pro sihs, lith. szeszi<BR>(n. m. pl., fem. szezios), slav. sʽes-tj (subst. fem.), cambro-brit.<BR>chwech, armor. chuech, hib. se 6, seas-gat<BR>60, v. gramm. 314., Pictet p. 141.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=360-1b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

