सत्|सन्त्|संत्<BR>सत् (fem. ई, Part. praes. r. अस् esse, v. gr. 365. et 594.)<BR>1) qui est. H. 4.3. BR. 3.18.<BR>2) honus, probus, praecipuus.<BR>SA. 3.12. BR. 2.26. H. 1.21. (Lat. -sens, sent-is<BR>in prae-sens, ab-sens, acc. -sentem = सन्तम्, lith.<BR>nom. m. esaṅs, f. esanti, acc. m. esantiṅ; gr. ὤν, jon.<BR>ἐών ex ἐσών, Them. ἐσοντ.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=365-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सतत|सततं<BR>सतत (ut videtur, mutilatum e सन्तत part. pass. r. तन्<BR>praef. सम्) aeternus. Acc. neut. सततम् Adv. semper,<BR>aeterne. BH. 6.10.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=365-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

