सद्<BR>1. सद् 1. vel 6. P. (in tempp. special. substituit सोद्, part.<BR>pass. सन्न; in dial. Vêd. etiam cl. 2. unde सत्सि, v.<BR>praef. आ et cf. lith. sếd-mi)<BR>1) sidere, considere, sinken;<BR>TROP. tabescere, fatiscere, perire. MAN. 4.191.: {#paNke<BR>gOr iva sIdati#}; N. 9.26.: सीदन्त्य् अङ्गानि सर्वशः;<BR>16.20.: न शोकेना ऽपि सीदति; SA. 5.46.: {#santo na<BR>sIdanti#}; R. Schl. II.41.8.: {#putraSokAgnisantaptaH sasAda<BR>gatacetanaH#}; MAH. 2.237.: राष्ट्रन् न सीदति; RAGH. 7.61.:<BR>सन्नशत्रुम्.<BR>2) considere, sedem capere. RIGV. 13.9.:<BR>बर्हिः सीदन्तु «in stragulo considunto».<BR>3) sedere,<BR>commorari. RIGV. 14.11.: अग्ने यज्ञेषु सीदसि.<BR>— Caus.<BR>1) facere ut qu. sidat, cadat. DR. 8.29.: {#sAditAH<BR>savyasAcinA#}.<BR>2) pulsare, percutere. RAGH. 7.41.:<BR>यैः सादिताः (schol. हताः)…{#tAn eva sAmarzitayA<BR>pratyAjaGnuH#}.<BR>3) ponere, collocare. RIGV. 15.4.: {#agne<BR>devA~ ihA ''vaha sAdayA trizu yonizu#} «Agnis! deos<BR>huc advehe colloca eos in locis tribus». (Goth. SAT sedere,<BR>sita, sat, sêtum, v. gr. comp. 109^a).<BR>1). 605.; satja<BR>pono = Caus. सादयामि, gr. comp. 109^a).<BR>6); germ.<BR>vet. SAZ sedere, sizu, saz, sâzumes; seziu pono; lith.<BR>sếd-mi sedeo, sodinu planto; slav. sjadû consido, ϰαϑί-ζομαι,<BR>sad-i-ti plantare = Caus., v. gr. comp. 505.; lat.<BR>sîdo; sedeo nititur formâ Caus. सादयामि; gr. ἙΔ, ἕδος, ἕζομαι;<BR>hib. suidhim sedeo, suidhiughaim «I set,<BR>plant» = Caus. सादयामि, mutato य् in gh; saidhe, saidhiste<BR>«a seat». Vid. 2. सद्.)<BR>c. अव sidere, tabescere, perire. SA. 5.47.: {#nA 'vasIdanti<BR>santaH#}; MAN. 4.187.: अवसीदन्न् अपि क्षुधा; HIT. 9.5.:<BR>अवसन्नायां रजन्याम्. Etiam A. MAH. 1.5184.:<BR>अवसीदेत. — Caus. facere ut qu. sidat, tabescat; deprimere.<BR>BH. 6.5.<BR>c. अव praef. वि id. MAH. 3.713. 823.<BR>c. आ<BR>1) considere, s'asseoir. RIGV. 26.4.: आ नो बर्हिः<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=366-b" target="_blank">Page366-b+ 37</a>]<BR>…सीदन्तु «in nostro stragulo considunto».<BR>2) sedere,<BR>assidere. RIGV. 12.4.: देवैर् आसत्सि बर्हिषि.<BR>c. उत् sidere, perire. BH. 3.24.: उत्सीदेयुर् इमे लोकाः;<BR>SU. 2.22.: उत्सन्नोत्सवयज्ञाच बभूव वसुधा; BH. 1.44.<BR>— Caus. उत्सादयामि destruere, evertere. BH. 1.43.:<BR>उत्साद्यन्ते जातिधर्माः.<BR>c. उत् praef. प्र Caus. i. q. Caus. praec. MAN. 9.261.<BR>c. उत् praef. सम् Caus. id. MAH. 3.88321.<BR>c. नि<BR>1) considere, s'asseoir, sich niedersetzen. N. 10.5.<BR>SA. 5.5. 6.: निषसाद महीतले. — निषण्ण (v. gr. 607.)<BR>adnisus, innisus aliquâ re. UR. 68.13.: {#nIpaskanDanizaRRas<BR>tizWati#}.<BR>2) A. sidere, tabescere. MAH. 3.333.:<BR>निषीदमानम्.<BR>c. प्र<BR>1) propendere, favere, propitium esse. BH. 11.25.:<BR>प्रसीद देवेश; 31.: देववर प्रसीद; N. 12.130.: {#taTA<BR>naH…maRiBadraH prasIdatu#}. — Cum infin. RAGH. 2.45.<BR>— प्रसन्न propitius. H. 1.45.: प्रसन्नास् ते देवाः; R. Schl. I.18.17.:<BR>प्रसन्नो ऽस्मि ते. — Etiam A. MAH. 1.4700.:<BR>प्रसीदस्व.<BR>2) clarum, serenum fieri. MAN. 6.67.:<BR>वारि प्रसीदति; RAGH. 3.14.: {#diSaH prasedur maruto<BR>vavuH#}. TROP. serenum, hilarem, laetum, alacrem animo<BR>fieri, exhilarari. MAN. 2.54.: हृष्येत् प्रसीदेच्च. — प्रसन्न<BR>clarus, serenus. N. 12.112.: नदीम् प्रसन्नसलिलाम्.<BR>— Caus. P. propitium reddere. R. Schl. I.66.24.: {#devagaRAn<BR>sarvAn tapasA 'ham prasAdayam#}; MAN. 11.205.<BR>A. 9.29. — ATM. supplicare, orare. BH. 11.44.: {#prasAdaye<BR>tvAm aham#}; SA. 1.16.: {#prasAdayAmAsa punaH kzipram<BR>etad Bavatv iti#} (v. gr. 458.); MAH. 1.4325.:<BR>प्रसादये त्वाम्; 3.1629. R. Schl. II.62.7. (Cf. hib.<BR>forsuidhe «steady, mild, meek», forsanaim «I shine»,<BR>fursan «flame of fire», fursain «evident», fursannaim<BR>«I kindle», v. Pictet p. 91.)<BR>c. प्र praef. अभि<BR>1) Caus. propitium reddere, propitiare,<BR>placare. MAH. 3.14063.<BR>2) exhilarare, consolari. R. Schl. II.77.24.:<BR>सुमन्त्रश्च शत्रुघ्नम् उत्थाप्या ऽभिप्रसाद्यच.<BR>c. प्र praef. सम् favere, propitium esse. R. Schl. II.26.34.<BR>— Caus. propitiare. MAH. 3.14039.<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-a" target="_blank">Page367-a+ 37</a>]<BR>c. वि<BR>1) sidere, tabescere, perire. MAH. 4.1953.: {#sIdanti<BR>mama prARA mano vihvalatI 'va me#}.<BR>2) moerore,<BR>dolore affligi, conturbari, perturbari, consternari, deliquium<BR>animi pati, animo linqui. MAH. 3.448.: {#taM vizIdantam<BR>AjYAya…amArayat#}; 3075.: {#vyasane tvam<BR>mahArAja na vizIditum arhasi#}; R. Schl. II.77.8.:<BR>विष्टनन् विषसाद ह; 107.19.: मा विषीद; BH. 1.28.<BR>— विषण्ण (v. gr. 607.) perturbatus, consternatus. R. Schl. I.40.24. 48.25.:<BR>विषण्णवदन; UR. 43.3.: {#urvaSI saha<BR>saKyA vizaRRA#}. — Caus. moerore, dolore afficere,<BR>conturbare, consternare. MAH. 3.3076. 2.718. R. Schl. II.7.18. 53.31.<BR>Vid. विषाद, विषादिन्.<BR>c. सम् i. q. simpl. MAN. 4.33.: संसीदन् क्षुधा.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=366-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सद्<BR>2. सद् 1. et 10. P. सदामि, सादयामि ire. (Slav. chod-i-ti<BR>ire, is-chod ἔξοδος (v. gr. comp. 255.m.); gr. ὅδος;<BR>fortasse goth. sandja mitto, nostrum sende = Caus. insertâ<BR>nasali, servato d propter antecedentem liquidam, v.<BR>gr. comp. 90.)<BR>c. आ<BR>1) adire, aggredi, appropinquare. N. 10.18.: {#AsasAda<BR>saBoddeSe vikoSaN KaNgam#}; 13.45.: पुरम् आसादयन्;<BR>17.4.: इयम् आसादिता बाला तव पुत्रनिवेशने;<BR>H. 1.15.: पथि गच्छन्तम् आसेदुः. Hostiliter aggredi.<BR>H. 4.2.: माम् आसादय दुर्बुद्धे. — आसन्न aggressus,<BR>qui accessit, appropinquavit, propinquus. HIT. 38.22.:<BR>जलासन्नतरुः; 68.11.: {#atrA ''sanne sarasi…<BR>snAti#}; pass. quem accessit aliquis, inde indutus, praeditus<BR>(v. इ praef. उप, अनु). NALOD. 1.37.: स्वमायासन्न.<BR>2) obtinere. MAH. 3.10472.: {#tAsu putram mahIpatiH kaYcin<BR>nA ''sAdayAmAsa#}.<BR>c. आ praef. अभि obtinere. MAH. 3.17101.<BR>c. आ praef. सम् adire, aggredi, appropinquare. N. 23.25.:<BR>समासाद्य पुत्रौ; MAH. 2.553.: कृष्णन् द्वारवत्यां समासदत्;<BR>SA. 5.5.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदन|सदनं<BR>सदन n. (r. सद् ire s. अन) domus, palatium. DR. 2.4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदस्<BR>सदस् n. (r. सद् s. अस्) coetus, conventus. UP. 76. (Gr.<BR>ἕδος, v. gr. comp. 128.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदा<BR>सदा (a stirpe demonstr. स s. दा) semper.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदागति|सदागतिः<BR>सदागति f. (semper itionem habens BAH. e सदा<BR>semper et गति itio) ventus.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदातन<BR>सदातन (f. ई, a सदा s. तन) sempiternus. AM.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सदृश|सदृशः<BR>सदृश (f. ई, e स q. v. et दृश, cf. gr. 287.) similis, c. gen.<BR>N. 1.27. 17.5. c. instr. BH. 16.15.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सद्मन्<BR>सद्मन् n. (r. सद् ire s. मन्) domus. (Cf. सदन.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सद्यस्<BR>सद्यस् (ut mihi videtur, e stirpe demonstr. स et द्यस्, quod<BR>correptum esse censeo ex obsoleto दिवस् dies, v. दिवस<BR>et cf. अद्य hodie) statim, momento. UR. 90.9.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सन्<BR>सन् 1. P. सनामि (सम्भक्तौ) colere, venerari, amare.<BR>8. P. A. सनोमि सन्वे (दाने) dare. In dial. Vêd. 1.<BR>et 8. adipisci, obtinere. RIGV. 73.5.: {#sanema vAjaM samiTezv<BR>aryaH#} «obtineamus in certaminibus cibum inimici»;<BR>5.9.: सनेद् इमं वाजम् इन्द्रः «Indras fruatur hoc cibo»;<BR>17.6.: तयोरिद् अवसा वयं सनेम «eorum auxilio<BR>nos divitiis fruamur»; 100.19.: {#aparihvftAH sanuyAma<BR>vAjam#} «non afflicti fruamur cibo».<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सना<BR>सना Adv. (ut mihi videtur, ex stirpe pronominali स q. v. s.<BR>ना, sicut विना a वि) semper. (Cf. anglo-sax. sin id.<BR>praesertim in initio compp.; germ. vet. sin id., v. Graff I.25.,<BR>goth. sin τοῦ sin-teins; nisi pertinent ad सम्, lat.<BR>sem-per.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनातन|सनातनः<BR>सनातन (fem. ई, a praec. suff. तन) sempiternus, aeternus,<BR>perpetuus. BR. 2.4. M. 7.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सनाथ<BR>सनाथ (BAH. e स cum et नाथ) conjunctus, praeditus. UR. 19.4.infr. 54.6.infr. 62.11.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=367-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

