स्वन्<BR>1. स्वन् 1. et 10. P. sonare. R. Schl. II.65.5.: {#vihagAH…<BR>sasvanuH#}; GHAT. 5.: जलदाः स्वनन्तः. (Vid. {#DraR,<BR>Dvan, kvaR#} et cf. lat. sono, hib. sian «a voice, sound,<BR>scream»; fortasse gr. ϕωνή e σϕωνή, v. स्व. Lith. zwanu<BR>sono et slav. ζveniû magis cum क्वण् quam cum स्वन्<BR>conveniunt, mutato k in g, deinde in z, ζ = ज्.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=394-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

