स्वसृ<BR>स्वसृ f. (in casibus fortibus स्वसार्, v. gr. 180.; ut videtur,<BR>e स्व suus et सृ i. e. सार् pro स्तृ, स्तार् = स्त्री femina,<BR>cujus t servatum est in linguis germanicis et slav.,<BR>v. स्वजन, श्वशुर, श्वश्रू et Pott. 2.554.) soror. H. 1.31.<BR>(Goth. svistar, germ. vet. suëstar, nostrum Schwester,<BR>angl. sister; slav. sestra, lith. sessů per assim. e sestů,<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">Page396-a+ 37</a>]<BR>gen. sesser-s, pl. nom. sesser-es; lat. soror e sosor,<BR>suostor, sorôrem = स्वसारम्; cambro-brit. chwaer,<BR>v. Pictet p. 73. Huc etiam traxerim hib. piuthar, ita ut<BR>mutilatum sit e spiusthar, mutato v in p sicut in speur<BR>coelum = स्वर् q. v.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=395-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्क्<BR>स्वस्क् 1. A. (गत्याम्) ire, se movere.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्ति<BR>स्वस्ति (e सु et अस्ति existentia, a r. अस् s. ति) Wohlsein,<BR>salus, felicitas. In classicâ linguâ Indecl. vel potius<BR>neut. quod solum in nom. et acc. invenitur. N. 12.120.<BR>DR. 9.23. A. 2.13. 10.41. BH. 11.21. — In dialecto<BR>Vêd. declinatur, e. c. RIGV. 1.9.: स्वस्तये felicitatis<BR>causâ.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्तिवाचन|स्वस्तिवाचनं<BR>स्वस्तिवाचन n. (e praec. et वाचन a Caus. r. वच् s.<BR>अन)<BR>1) precatio salutis, v. वच् Caus.<BR>2) ritus quidam<BR>sacer, Wils. «a religious rite preparatory to any important<BR>observance, in which the Brahmans strew boiled<BR>rice on the ground, and invoke the blessings of the gods<BR>on the ceremony about to commence». UR. 45.1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वस्थ|स्वस्थः<BR>स्वस्थ (in se stans, versans, e स्व et स्थ)<BR>1) sui<BR>compos. N. 2.1. 5.6. 7. BH. 14.24.<BR>2) sanus, salvus, valens.<BR>SA. 5.81. 109.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वागत|स्वागतं<BR>स्वागत n. (KARM. e सु bene et आगत n. aggressus) salutatio<BR>(Willkommen, welcome). N. 12.68.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वातन्त्र्य|स्वातंत्र्य|स्वातंत्र्यं|स्वातन्त्र्यं<BR>स्वातन्त्र्य n. (a स्वतन्त्र s. य) libertas, liberum arbitrium.<BR>HIT. 28.16. 69.14.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वाद्<BR>स्वाद् 1. A. 10. P. i. q. स्वद्. — स्वादनीय gustandus,<BR>sapidus, jucundi, suavis saporis. IN. 1.26. (Vid. {#svad,<BR>svAdu#} et cf. gr. ἥδομαι, ἧδος, ἁνδάνω, cambro-brit.<BR>chwaethu gustare, armor. chwaesa odorari, v. Pictet<BR>p. 73.)<BR>c. आ 10. P. gustare. R. Schl. I.9.36.: {#tAny AsvAdya sa<BR>…anAsvAditapUrvARi#}. — आस्वाद्य gustandus, jucundi,<BR>suavis saporis. HIT. 8.12. Vid. आस्वाद, आस्वादन.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वादु|स्वादुः<BR>स्वादु (fem. स्वादु et स्वाद्वी dulcis, suavis, jucundus.<BR>(Anglo-sax. svet dulcis, germ. vet. suazi, suozi id., nostrum<BR>süʃs, goth. sutizô dulcius; lith. saldùs dulcis e<BR>[<a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-b" target="_blank">Page396-b+ 37</a>]<BR>sladùs, mutato v in l, v. gr. comp. 20., slav. сΛадъкъ<BR>sladk id., gr. ἡδύς, lat. suavis e suadus ejecto d, adjecto<BR>i; vid. स्वद्.)<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-a" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वाधीन|स्वाधीनः<BR>स्वाधीन Adj. (e स्व et अधीन) sibi ipsi subjectus, sui proprius.<BR>Lass. 90.15.: स्वाधीनयौवना सुभ्रूः. — Nostri<BR>proprius, qui in nostrâ potestate. HIT. 122.3. 4.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

स्वाध्याय|स्वाध्यायः<BR>स्वाध्याय m. (e स्व proprius et अध्याय lectio a rad. इ<BR>praef. अधि suff. अ) tacita vel susurrans lectio Vêdorum.<BR>SU. 2.22. BH. 4.28. 16.1.<BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslp?dict=BOP&page=396-b" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://dub.sh/cslc?dict=bop" target="_blank">Correction</a>

